roblems, passing the audition process with flying colors, but she was able to blaze through it. Her bright and fun personality in the interview already had the team eating out of the palm of her hand, but after her performance in the ring, it was a no-brainer. She was signed on the spot.\r\n\r\n\"This is the most exciting day of my life,\" a tearful Storm said after hugs were exchanged between her, Eric James, Joe Morton and the rest of the WCFA team Saturday afternoon at a signing ceremony in the ballroom of WCFA Academy. \"To be here in the biggest and best wrestling company in the world means everything to me. This is where I want to spend the rest of my life. If there was one promotion I always dreamed of going to, it was this one.\"\r\n\r\nWCFA is absolutely excited to have Toni Storm on board. If you haven\'t seen her in action, stay tuned, because you will soon find out why WCFA went out of their way to sign her.','WCFA Officially Signs Toni Storm','One of the most dynamic and talented young women in sports entertainment joins the WCFA family.','inherit','closed','closed','','38-revision-v1','','','2017-12-22 21:31:18','2017-12-22 21:31:18','',38,'http://wcfa.lo/2017/12/22/38-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(71,1,'2017-12-22 21:33:45','2017-12-22 21:33:45','Quisque sodales, tortor quis convallis facilisis, leo purus consectetur nibh, varius egestas nunc enim non nibh. Nullam dictum sapien non dolor imperdiet, ac lobortis nisi volutpat. Suspendisse convallis, ex non auctor molestie, enim enim molestie leo, non dapibus tortor nisl eu ipsum. Suspendisse potenti. Pellentesque tempor tortor non sem malesuada, vitae faucibus purus scelerisque. Praesent erat metus, egestas convallis hendrerit et, cursus eget quam. Interdum et malesuada fames ac ante ipsum primis in faucibus. Sed in lorem sagittis, faucibus ipsum vel, rhoncus ante. Vestibulum luctus auctor felis at viverra. Praesent ex nunc, sollicitudin pretium ullamcorper at, varius at odio. Sed id mauris in nunc 