36','2017-12-22 23:27:36','',76,'http://wcfa.lo/2017/12/22/76-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(80,1,'2017-12-23 00:01:06','2017-12-23 00:01:06','Toni Storm is one of the brightest young stars to arrive on the scene of women\'s sports entertainment in the past couple of years. She has been a lifelong wrestling fan and has stated on multiple occasions that she was inspired by watching the likes of WCFA Hall of Famers such as the Cavity Monster and Chin Kim growing up with her two brothers in Aukland, New Zealand, which is her hometown.\r\n\r\nStorm began wrestling at the tender age of just 13 in front of crowds of about 50 to 100 people. As humble as those beginnings were, she quickly rose to prominence, touring all over Europe, the United States and Japan, wowing crowds with her prodigious technical skill, athleticism and ring savvy. She was noticed by WCFA Head Talent Scout Eric James in 2016 and flown to Los Angeles at WCFA headquarters for an interview. The WCFA Recruitment Team then sent her to WCFA Academy for the notoriously difficult auditioning process and she not only was able to handle everything thrown at her with no problems, passing the audition process with flying colors, but she was able to blaze through it. Her bright and fun personality in the interview already had the team eating out of the palm of her hand, but after her performance in the ring, it was a no-brainer. She was signed on the spot.\r\n\r\n\"This is the most exciting day of my life,\" a tearful Storm said after hugs were exchanged between her, Eric James, Joe Morton and the rest of the WCFA team Saturday afternoon at a signing ceremony in the ballroom of WCFA Academy. \"To be here in the biggest and best wrestling company in the world means everything to me. This is where I want to spend the rest of my life. If there was one promotion I always dreamed of going to, it was this one.\"\r\n\r\nWCFA is absolutely excited to have Toni Storm on board. If you haven\'t seen her in action, stay tuned, because you will soon find out why WCFA went out of their way to sign her.','WCFA Officially Signs Toni Storm','One of the most dynamic and talented young women in sports entertainment joins the WCFA family.','inherit','closed','closed','','38-revision-v1','','','2017-12-23 00:01:06','2017-12-23 00:01:06','',38,'http://wcfa.lo/2017/12/23/38-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0);
